20/02/2006
SHKODRA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu and Montenegrin counterpart Filip Vujanovic held an informal meeting on Sunday (19 February) and agreed to strengthen already solid bilateral ties. 
Aides say Moisiu and Vujanovic particularly focused on joint cross-border projects relating to infrastructure, the environment and tourism.
On Monday, meanwhile, Moisiu meets with visiting Moldovan counterpart Vladimir Voronin. 
They are expected to discuss issues related to bilateral co-operation and ways to enhance trade and economic co-operation. 
Voronin travels on to Skopje Tuesday. 
(Albanian President Web site, Tanjug, Makfax - 19/02/06)
